# Four root causes explain the pilot-to-production failure rate
@type: comparison

@compare:
  header: Root Cause | Prevalence | Impact | Fix
  row: No AI platform (each team builds own infrastructure) | 78% of orgs | High — duplication, no reuse | Build shared MLOps platform
  row: Change management absent (business won't adopt) | 65% | High — models built but not used | Embed change in every use case
  row: Data access barriers (months to get training data) | 71% | High — slows all development | Data governance reform
  row: No value measurement framework (unknown ROI) | 83% | Medium — no prioritization signal | Standardize value tracking

@exhibit: Exhibit 2 — AI Scaling Barrier Analysis
@source: McKinsey QuantumBlack AI Scaling Research, 2024

@notes: Data access barriers are the most common and the most fixable. A data access SLA (target: 5 business days for approved use cases) removes the single biggest development bottleneck.

