# Enterprise AI scaling requires a centralized AI factory model
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## AI Factory Infrastructure
  - Shared MLOps platform: training, deployment, monitoring
  - Feature store: reusable feature engineering across models
  - Model registry: governance, versioning, and audit trail
  - Compute governance: GPU/TPU allocation and chargebacks
  - AI security: adversarial testing, bias monitoring, explainability

@col:
  ## AI Factory Operating Model
  - Central AI team of 40–60 experts embedded across BUs
  - Center-of-Excellence model: standards + embedded resources
  - Portfolio management: prioritize top 10 use cases quarterly
  - Value tracking: standardized P&L impact measurement
  - Talent pipeline: AI fluency training for all knowledge workers

@notes: The AI factory is not just a technology concept — it is an operating model. The technology without the operating model produces the same pilot diffusion problem in a more expensive wrapper.

